Until there is a seamless, idiot-proof, "big button" solution for using PGP encryption, the fact remains that it's just too hard for your average (non-IT-professional) person to use.Online webmail providers aren't going to build it into their systems because then they wouldn't be able to mine emails for ad targeting. What's needed is an easy-to-use, cross-platform, client-agnostic, PGP encryption application. Something as easy to use as Facebook, that automatically shares everyone's public keys with all their friends and contacts, and automatically encrypts all communications. If someone gets it right they could make a fortune.
