Quote:Something as easy to use as Facebook, that automatically shares everyone's public keys with all their friends and contacts, and automatically encrypts all communicationsThe problem with anything that automatically shares/befriends/encrypts in this situation is that it might automatically or accidentally share your private key with people you don't want it to. I think that is the big issue. If your private key is in the cloud, you lose, so anything cloud/webmail style just plain doesn't work. You have to store your keys locally, or keep them encrypted, which starts to get back into 'lots of hassle' territory.That is the real problem that needs solving. Keeping your private key safe enough and accessible enough. After that, the rest is trivial.
