An option I missed is a solution for those that want to keep using web-based clients.Mailvelope is a very easy way to set up PGP: it's a Chrome extension (a Firefox addon is on its way) that will encrypt/decrypt your mails locally. It's extremely easy and works great. It's a young project though, so some things are missing: signing messages and verrifying them is not yet supported. But basic encryption works great, and the integration with any webbased client (litterelly every client: you can select any text-field on a page and encrypt the text you type in it) is really really polished.http://mailvelope.com/
